    "description": "I make travel itineraries for a living, so here's exactly how to do Lisbon without missing a single miradouro, custard tart or fado moment. 4 walking routes covering 30 stops with the time and price for every one, AND a free Lisbon map you can download. 🚶 ITINERARY 1 Classic Lisbon Jardim do Príncipe Real — free Miradouro de São Pedro de Alcântara — free Igreja de São Roque — free (€2.50 museum) Convento do Carmo — €7 Elevador de Santa Justa — €6 Praça do Comércio — free Arco da Rua Augusta — €4 Pink Street — free Time Out Market Lisboa — free entry Lisbon Sunset Boat Party — cruise 🛥️ 🚶 ITINERARY 2 Castle & Views Sé de Lisboa — free (€4 cloister) Miradouro de Santa Luzia — free Miradouro das Portas do Sol — free Alfama (the old quarter) — free Igreja de São Vicente de Fora — €8 Panteão Nacional — €8 Feira da Ladra (flea market) — free Castelo de São Jorge — €15 Miradouro da Graça — free Miradouro da Senhora do Monte — free (BEST sunset spot 🌅) 🚶 ITINERARY 3 — Belém Torre de Belém — €8 Padrão dos Descobrimentos — €8 Mosteiro dos Jerónimos — €12 Pastéis de Belém — €1.40/tart (the OG 🥮) MAAT — €11 (rooftop free) 🚶 ITINERARY 4 Aqueducts & Gardens Museu Calouste Gulbenkian — €10 (garden free) Parque Eduardo VII — free Estufa Fria — €3 Aqueduto das Águas Livres — €4 Mysterious Egypt Show — €18 Every stop is walkable to the next bring comfy shoes, Lisbon's hills don't play 🥵 📌 save this for your trip 👯 send it to your Lisbon travel buddy 🌍 comment which city you want next 🗺️ Get my FREE Lisbon map + my hotel tips, restaurants & full guide → link in my bio 👉 #lisbontrip #portugaltravel #citybreak #europetravel #travelhacks",
