    "description": "3 days in Lisbon itinerary #lisbon #solofemaletraveler \nExplore Lisbon in 3 days with this solo female traveler itinerary. Discover unique places to eat and top things to do in Lisbon.\nPlanning a trip to Lisbon? This 3-day itinerary is perfect for solo female travelers looking to experience the best of the city. Discover unique culinary gems and uncover must-do activities that will make your Lisbon adventure unforgettable.\n\n**Day 1: Historic Charm and Bairro Alto Nights**\nStart your Lisbon exploration in the historic Alfama district. Wander through its narrow, winding streets, listen to Fado music, and visit the iconic São Jorge Castle for panoramic city views. For lunch, seek out a traditional tasca for some authentic Portuguese cuisine. In the afternoon, take Tram 28 for a scenic ride through the city's most picturesque neighborhoods. As evening approaches, head to the Bairro Alto, known for its vibrant nightlife and diverse dining options. Enjoy dinner at one of the many unique eateries before experiencing the lively atmosphere of its bars.\n\n**Day 2: Belém's Discoveries and Riverside Views**\nDedicate your second day to the historic district of Belém. Marvel at the Jerónimos Monastery and the Belém Tower, both UNESCO World Heritage sites that speak volumes of Portugal's Age of Discovery. Don't miss trying the famous Pastéis de Belém from the original bakery. In the afternoon, enjoy a leisurely walk along the Tagus River or visit the Monument to the Discoveries. Consider a sunset cruise for breathtaking views of the city from the water.\n\n**Day 3: Modern Lisbon and Day Trip Options**\nExplore the modern side of Lisbon in the Parque das Nações, built for Expo '98. Visit the Oceanário de Lisboa, one of Europe's largest aquariums, or take a cable car ride for stunning river views. Alternatively, if you're looking for a change of scenery, consider a day trip. Sintra, with its romantic palaces and mystical forests, is a popular choice. Cascais, a charming seaside town, offers a more relaxed coastal experience. Whichever you choose, ensure you allow ample time to soak in the distinct atmosphere of these nearby destinations before returning to Lisbon for your final evening.",
